**Sec. 70001. References to the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, etc.**  
This section clarifies that all amendments in the bill are to be treated as changes to the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, unless otherwise specified. It explicitly excludes the application of Section 15 of the Code, which governs rate change rules, to any tax rate adjustments made by this bill. The provision ensures consistency in interpreting the bill’s amendments as direct updates to the Code. This applies to all sections of the bill, including those modifying tax rates, deductions, and credits.

**Sec. 70101. Extension and Enhancement of Reduced Rates.**  
The bill permanently extends the 2018–2025 reduced tax rates for all taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025, removing the prior expiration date. It modifies the inflation adjustment for rate brackets, applying it solely to the thresholds for the 12% and 22% brackets. The change ensures that the 12% and 22% brackets are adjusted annually based on inflation, starting from 2025. The amendment applies to all individual taxpayers and takes effect for taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70102. Extension and Enhancement of Increased Standard Deduction.**  
The standard deduction is permanently extended for taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024, removing the prior expiration. The base deduction is increased to $23,625 for single filers and $15,750 for married filing separately, up from $18,000 and $12,000, respectively. The increase applies to all taxpayers and is indexed for inflation starting in 2025. The change takes effect for taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70103. Termination of Deduction for Personal Exemptions Other Than Temporary Senior Deduction.**  
The personal exemption deduction is permanently eliminated for all taxpayers except for a new $6,000 deduction for seniors. The senior deduction applies to individuals aged 65 or older, or their spouses, for taxable years beginning before January 1, 2029. The deduction is reduced by 6% of modified adjusted gross income (MAGI) exceeding $75,000 ($150,000 for joint filers). The deduction requires a valid Social Security number and applies only to joint returns.

**Sec. 70104. Extension and Enhancement of Increased Child Tax Credit.**  
The expanded Child Tax Credit is permanently extended, increasing the credit to $2,200 per qualifying child, up from $2,000. The refundable portion is capped at $1,400 per child and is adjusted annually for inflation starting in 2025. The credit requires the inclusion of both the taxpayer’s and child’s Social Security numbers on the tax return. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70105. Extension and Enhancement of Deduction for Qualified Business Income.**  
The deduction for qualified business income (QBI) is permanently extended, increasing the phase-in threshold to $75,000 ($150,000 for joint filers). A new minimum $400 deduction is guaranteed for any taxpayer with at least $1,000 in active QBI. The $400 and $1,000 thresholds are indexed for inflation starting in 2026. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70106. Extension and Enhancement of Increased Estate and Gift Tax Exemption Amounts.**  
The estate and gift tax exemption is permanently increased to $15 million per individual, up from $5 million. The exemption applies to estates of decedents dying and gifts made after December 31, 2025. The change eliminates the prior sunset provision and applies retroactively to 2026. The exemption is indexed for inflation starting in 2026.

**Sec. 70107. Extension of Increased Alternative Minimum Tax Exemption Amounts and Modification of Phaseout Thresholds.**  
The AMT exemption is permanently extended, with the $109,400 (single) and $70,300 (married filing separately) thresholds adjusted for inflation starting in 2026. The phaseout threshold for the $1 million exemption is increased to $1 million, with the phaseout rate raised to 50% from 25%. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70108. Extension and Modification of Limitation on Deduction for Qualified Residence Interest.**  
The mortgage interest deduction is permanently extended, removing the prior expiration. The deduction now includes mortgage insurance premiums as interest, and the $750,000 loan limit applies to all loans taken after December 31, 2024. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70109. Extension and Modification of Limitation on Casualty Loss Deduction.**  
The casualty loss deduction is permanently extended, removing the prior expiration. The deduction now applies to losses from state-declared disasters, including hurricanes, floods, and wildfires. The definition of “State declared disaster” includes all U.S. states, territories, and the District of Columbia. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70110. Termination of Miscellaneous Itemized Deductions Other Than Educator Expenses.**  
All miscellaneous itemized deductions (e.g., unreimbursed employee expenses, tax preparation fees) are permanently eliminated, except for educator expenses. The deduction for educator expenses is expanded to include coaches and nonathletic instructional equipment. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70111. Limitation on Tax Benefit of Itemized Deductions.**  
Itemized deductions are reduced by 2/37 of the lesser of the total deductions or the amount by which taxable income exceeds the 37% bracket threshold. The limitation applies after all other deduction limits and does not apply to the QBI deduction. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70112. Extension and Modification of Qualified Transportation Fringe Benefits.**  
The exclusion for qualified transportation fringe benefits is permanently extended, removing the prior expiration. The exclusion now includes bicycle commuting reimbursements and is capped at $270 per month. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70113. Extension and Modification of Limitation on Deduction and Exclusion for Moving Expenses.**  
The deduction and exclusion for moving expenses are permanently extended, removing the prior expiration. The exclusion now applies to members of the intelligence community who relocate due to a change in assignment. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70114. Extension and Modification of Limitation on Wagering Losses.**  
Wagering losses are limited to 90% of wagering gains, with losses only deductible to the extent of gains. The change applies to all taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70115. Extension and Enhancement of Increased Limitation on Contributions to ABLE Accounts.**  
The annual contribution limit for ABLE accounts is permanently increased to $16,000, up from $15,000, with inflation adjustments starting in 2026. The change applies to contributions made after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70116. Extension and Enhancement of Savers Credit Allowed for ABLE Contributions.**  
The savers credit for ABLE contributions is increased to $2,100, up from $2,000, and applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2026. The credit is available for contributions to ABLE accounts and other retirement savings. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2026.

**Sec. 70117. Extension of Rollovers from Qualified Tuition Programs to ABLE Accounts Permitted.**  
Rollovers from 529 plans to ABLE accounts are permanently permitted, removing the prior expiration. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70118. Extension of Treatment of Certain Individuals Performing Services in the Sinai Peninsula and Enhancement to Include Additional Areas.**  
The exclusion for income earned in hazardous duty areas is permanently extended, now including Kenya, Mali, Burkina Faso, and Chad. The change applies to members of the Armed Forces entitled to special pay under 37 U.S.C. §310. The change takes effect on January 1, 2026.

**Sec. 70119. Extension and Modification of Exclusion from Gross Income of Student Loans Discharged on Account of Death or Disability.**  
Discharged student loans due to death or disability are permanently excluded from gross income. The exclusion applies to both federal and private education loans. The change requires inclusion of the taxpayer’s Social Security number on the return. The change applies to discharges after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70120. Limitation on Individual Deductions for Certain State and Local Taxes, etc.**  
The SALT deduction is permanently limited to $40,000 for 2025, increasing to $40,400 in 2026, then rising by 1% annually until 2030, when it drops to $10,000. The limit is reduced by 30% of MAGI exceeding $500,000 ($250,000 for separate filers). The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70201. No Tax on Tips.**  
Tips are permanently excluded from taxable income, with a $25,000 annual deduction limit. The deduction is reduced by $100 for every $1,000 of MAGI exceeding $150,000 ($300,000 for joint filers). The deduction applies to non-itemizers and requires a valid Social Security number. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70202. No Tax on Overtime.**  
Overtime compensation is permanently excluded from taxable income, with a $12,500 annual deduction limit ($25,000 for joint filers). The deduction is reduced by $100 for every $1,000 of MAGI exceeding $150,000 ($300,000 for joint filers). The deduction applies to non-itemizers and requires a valid Social Security number. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70203. No Tax on Car Loan Interest.**  
Interest on qualified passenger vehicle loans is permanently excluded from taxable income, with a $10,000 annual limit. The deduction is reduced by $200 for every $1,000 of MAGI exceeding $100,000 ($200,000 for joint filers). The vehicle must be a car, van, SUV, pickup, or motorcycle with a gross vehicle weight under 14,000 pounds. The change applies to loans incurred after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70204. Trump Accounts and Contribution Pilot Program.**  
Trump Accounts are established as tax-advantaged retirement accounts for individuals under 18, with contributions limited to $5,000 annually. Employer contributions are limited to $2,500 annually. The Trump Accounts Contribution Pilot Program provides a $1,000 payment per eligible child born between 2025 and 2028. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70301. Full Expensing for Certain Business Property.**  
Businesses may fully expense the cost of qualified property placed in service after January 19, 2025, with a 40% or 60% election for specified plants. The change applies to property acquired after January 19, 2025. The transition election applies to taxable years ending after January 19, 2025. The change applies to all eligible property.

**Sec. 70302. Full Expensing of Domestic Research and Experimental Expenditures.**  
Domestic research and experimental expenditures are fully deductible in the year incurred, with an optional 60-month amortization election. The change applies to amounts paid or incurred in taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024. The change applies to all domestic research, including software development. The change applies to all eligible taxpayers.

**Sec. 70303. Modification of Limitation on Business Interest.**  
The business interest deduction limitation is permanently extended, removing the prior expiration. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024. The floor plan financing rule is expanded to include trailers and campers. The change applies to all eligible taxpayers.

**Sec. 70304. Extension and Enhancement of Paid Family and Medical Leave Credit.**  
The paid family and medical leave credit is permanently extended, with a 100% credit for wages paid or insurance premiums. The credit applies to employers with a written policy. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70305. Exceptions from Limitations on Deduction for Business Meals.**  
Business meals on fishing vessels and fish processing facilities are fully deductible, removing the 50% limit. The change applies to meals provided after December 31, 2025. The change applies to all eligible businesses.

**Sec. 70306. Increased Dollar Limitations for Expensing of Certain Depreciable Business Assets.**  
The Section 179 expensing limit is increased to $2.5 million, with a $4 million investment limit. The change applies to property placed in service in taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024. The change applies to all eligible businesses.

**Sec. 70307. Special Depreciation Allowance for Qualified Production Property.**  
Qualified production property placed in service after January 19, 2025, and before January 1, 2031, receives a 100% special depreciation allowance. The change applies to nonresidential real property used in manufacturing. The change applies to all eligible taxpayers.

**Sec. 70308. Enhancement of Advanced Manufacturing Investment Credit.**  
The advanced manufacturing investment credit is increased to 35%, up from 25%. The change applies to property placed in service after December 31, 2025. The change applies to all eligible manufacturers.

**Sec. 70309. Spaceports Are Treated Like Airports Under Exempt Facility Bond Rules.**  
Spaceports are treated as airports for purposes of exempt facility bonds. The change applies to obligations issued after the date of enactment. The change applies to all eligible spaceports.

**Sec. 70311. Modifications Related to Foreign Tax Credit Limitation.**  
Deductions under Section 250(a)(1)(B) are allocated to foreign source net CFC tested income. Interest and research expenses are not allocated to foreign income. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70312. Modifications to Determination of Deemed Paid Credit for Taxes Properly Attributable to Tested Income.**  
The deemed paid foreign tax credit is increased to 90%. A 10% disallowance applies to foreign taxes on previously taxed net CFC tested income. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70313. Sourcing Certain Income from the Sale of Inventory Produced in the United States.**  
Income from the sale of U.S.-produced inventory through foreign branches is treated as foreign-sourced, up to 50% of total income. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70321. Modification of Deduction for Foreign-Derived Deduction Eligible Income and Net CFC Tested Income.**  
The deduction for foreign-derived deduction eligible income is reduced to 33.34%, and the net CFC tested income deduction is reduced to 40%. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70322. Determination of Deduction Eligible Income.**  
Income from the sale of intangible property and depreciable assets is included in deduction eligible income. Expenses are limited to those properly allocable to such income. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70323. Rules Related to Deemed Intangible Income.**  
“Global intangible low-taxed income” is replaced with “net CFC tested income.” The tax-free deemed return on foreign investments is repealed. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70331. Extension and Modification of Base Erosion Minimum Tax Amount.**  
The base erosion minimum tax rate is increased to 10.5%. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025. The change applies to all eligible taxpayers.

**Sec. 70341. Coordination of Business Interest Limitation with Interest Capitalization Provisions.**  
Business interest limitation applies regardless of capitalization rules. Disallowed interest is carried forward and not treated as capitalizable. The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70342. Definition of Adjusted Taxable Income for Business Interest Limitation.**  
Adjusted taxable income includes income from Section 951(a), 951A(a), and 78, and deductions under 245A(a) and 250(a)(1)(B). The change applies to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70351. Permanent Extension of Look-Through Rule for Related Controlled Foreign Corporations.**  
The look-through rule for related controlled foreign corporations is permanently extended. The change applies to taxable years of foreign corporations beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70352. Repeal of Election for 1-Month Deferral in Determination of Taxable Year of Specified Foreign Corporations.**  
The 1-month deferral election is repealed. The change applies to taxable years of specified foreign corporations beginning after November 30, 2025.

**Sec. 70353. Restoration of Limitation on Downward Attribution of Stock Ownership in Applying Constructive Ownership Rules.**  
Downward attribution of stock ownership is restored, preventing U.S. persons from being treated as owning stock held by non-U.S. persons. The change applies to taxable years of foreign corporations beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70354. Modifications to Pro Rata Share Rules.**  
The pro rata share of subpart F income is determined based on stock ownership and period of ownership. The change applies to taxable years of foreign corporations beginning after December 31, 2025. [end of text]


